10/12/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Leaders of the Democratic League of Kosovo (LDK) on Tuesday (December 9th) managed to fill two long-vacant deputy minister posts. The party named Behxhet Brajshori as deputy minister of the Kosovo Security Forces, while Jonuz Kastrati will be deputy minister for trade and industry.
In other news, Tuesday marked the International Day against Corruption. A publication supported by the UNDP said courts are the most corrupt institutions in Kosovo. 
Wednesday marks International Human Rights Day, prompting the head of the OSCE mission in Kosovo, Austrian diplomat Werner Almhofer, to say Kosovo has passed several laws demonstrating its commitment to human rights. (Koha Ditore, Zeri, Kosova Sot, Express - 10/12/08)
